On Tue, Jun 1, 2010 at 4:49 AM, T.P. Stephens <doktortim(-at-)rockisland.com> wrote:

> If you should happen to set No. 1 on the No. 3 lobe which is retarded 3 degrees,
 the other 3 cylinders will be advanced 3 degrees from stock, meaning No. 3
 will then be advanced 6 degrees from it's normal 3 degrees retarded.

That's a limited production run of distributors with # 3 retarded, and
would not be on a type 4 engine unless someone put one on to replace
the original. Check your distributor model number at Old Volks Home. I
get a Bandwidth Exceeded message there right now, but it's nearly the
1st of the month, so should be back up soon.

